ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Item 1: I am confident of having a normal childbirth. Reverse scored
Notes: 1 = Very much; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Somewhat; 4 = Not at all; 99 = Decline to answer; 999 = data missing

ElementDescription: Item 2: I think my labor and delivery will go normally. Reverse scored
Notes: 1 = Very much; 2 = Moderately; 3 = Somewhat; 4 = Not at all; 99 = Decline to answer; 999 = data missing

ElementDescription: Item 3: I have a lot of fear regarding the health of my baby.
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = Somewhat; 3 = Moderately; 4 = Very much; 99 = Decline to answer; 999 = data missing

ElementDescription: Item 4: I am worried that the baby could be abnormal.
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = Somewhat; 3 = Moderately; 4 = Very much; 99 = Decline to answer; 999 = data missing

ElementDescription: Item 5: I am afraid that I will be harmed during delivery

ElementDescription: Item 6: I am concerned (worried) about how the baby is growing and developed inside me.
